				<p class="quote">Each day, we wake slightly altered, and the person we were yesterday is dead. So why, one could say, be afraid of death, when death comes all the time?</p>
				<p class="source">- John Updike</p>
			
		
			
		
			
		
			
		
			
			
			
				
